    {
      "id": "vpc-transit-gateway-children",
      "service": "networking/vpc",
      "enabled": true,
      "heavy": true,
      "_note": "Closes the transit-gateway CHILD writes (10): POST/DELETE for firewalls, firewall-connections, routing-rules, uplink-routing-rules, vpc-connections. (POST /v1/transit-gateways + PUT/DELETE /v1/transit-gateways/{id} are already covered elsewhere and out of scope.) Bodies from data/api_bodies.json (networking/vpc/createtransitgateway*, ...rule, ...uplinkrule, ...vpcconnection, ...firewall, ...firewallconnection). createtransitgatewayfirewallconnection body in api_bodies is the corrupt {\"_raw\":\"{transit_gateway_id}\"} -> replaced with a docs-best-guess {firewall_id} body. We create a real transit-gateway as the parent (capture $.transit_gateway.id UNPROVEN); each child create needs ids we may not have (a TGW firewall product, a peer VPC connection) so all children are optional+grouped+broad expect_status -> they record coverage even on 4xx. tgw_connection_vpc_id / vpc_id reference {vpc_id} (we adopt the shared VPC). routing_rule_id captures are soft. heavy:true (real TGW + VPC fallback are billable).",
